  "prompt": "If I have someone blocked on Instagram, and view their story, can they see I viewed it?",
  "response": "No, if you have someone blocked on Instagram and you view their story, they will **not** be able to see that you viewed it. When you block someone on Instagram, they are essentially cut off from seeing your activity or interacting with you on the platform. This includes not being able to see if you\u2019ve viewed their story.\n\nHowever, if you unblock them afterward, they still won\u2019t retroactively see that you viewed their story while you were blocked. Keep in mind that if you unblock them and interact with their content after that, they\u2019ll be able to see your activity moving forward.",
